<link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=CYBERCRIMES;1a47bf85.1410</link>   <description> ~With the usual apologies for cross posting~<br><br>1st International Conference on Cyber Security for Sustainable Society 2015<br><br>26-27th February 2015, Coventry, United Kingdom<br><br>Modern society aspires to be economically and socially sustainable.<br>The digital infrastructure underpinning our society allows us to achieve these goals by various mechanisms including online social networks, trust and reputation, peer-to-peer and content sharing, secure transactions and online voting. Such mechanisms however are at increasing risk from cyber attacks, industrial espionage, online fraud and government surveillance; each serving to undermine trust and security at different levels. This conference offers a unique platform to address the issues [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2014-10-02T09:14:23+01:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Gordon, Tim</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=CYBERCRIMES;1a47bf85.1410</dc:identifier> </item>   </rdf:RDF>
